ary reports, traders' accounts and maps" (The New York Review of Books). Volume II: A Century of Wonder examines the influence of that vast new body of information about Asia on the arts, institutions, literatures, and ideas of sixteenth-century Europe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEast and WestxHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aasia, exoticism, cultural exchange, trade, discovery, exploration, portugal, universality, harmony, renaissance, linguistics, language, botany, science, alchemy, chemistry, influence, patronage, atlas, ptolemy, geography, cartography, navigation, nautics, astronomy, engineering, technology, literature, humanism, cosmography, empire, drama, stairs, germany, netherlands, italy, siege, maritime, history, politics, government, nonfiction.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999z978311066785140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226467139423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226467139/original  a978-3-11-066785-1  University of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999c1990d1999  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles